  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contributing to the reduction of morbidity and mortality among vulnerable groups in most affected counties by severe acute food insecurity in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to reduce morbidity and mortality due to severe wasting among young children. This UNICEF project 1) admits 8,290 children into SAM treatment programmes and 2) provides 187,014 people with access to sufficient and safe water for drinking, cooking and/or personal hygiene among other activities. The project provides life-saving assistance to 187,014 people, including 44,883 women, 41,143 men, 100,988 children, and 1,870 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
